 ],
 "segments": [
  {
   "start": 0.0,
   "end": 3.66,
   "text": "There's one thing you must never do with chopsticks in China, stand them straight up"
  },
  {
   "start": 3.66,
   "end": 4.52,
   "text": "in your bowl of rice."
  },
  {
   "start": 4.92,
   "end": 7.22,
   "text": "Do it and you've just set a place for the dead."
  },
  {
   "start": 7.62,
   "end": 9.98,
   "text": "It's one of the deepest dining taboos in Chinese culture."
  },
  {
   "start": 10.56,
   "end": 12.0,
   "text": "And the reason is what it resembles."
  },
  {
   "start": 12.56,
   "end": 17.08,
   "text": "At funerals and ancestor rituals, a bowl of rice with incense and their chopsticks, standing"
  },
  {
   "start": 17.08,
   "end": 18.7,
   "text": "straight up, is offered to the deceased."
  },
  {
   "start": 19.18,
   "end": 20.16,
   "text": "It's a gift for the dead."
  },
  {
   "start": 20.58,
   "end": 24.38,
   "text": "So at a normal dinner, chopsticks jammed upright look exactly like a death offering."
  },
  {
   "start": 24.58,
   "end": 27.34,
   "text": "It's read as an omen, almost like inviting death to the table."
  },
  {
   "start": 27.34,
   "end": 32.08,
   "text": "Instead you lay your chopsticks flat, across the top of the bowl, or on a little rest."
  },
  {
   "start": 32.82,
   "end": 37.18,
   "text": "Tiny gesture, completely different meaning, and these death related taboos get taken even"
  },
  {
   "start": 37.18,
   "end": 41.68,
   "text": "more seriously during the 7th lunar month, ghost month, when spirits are said to roam"
  },
  {
   "start": 41.68,
   "end": 44.08,
   "text": "and people avoid anything that might invite bad luck."
  },
  {
   "start": 44.6,
   "end": 46.34,
   "text": "It's just two sticks and a bowl of rice."
  },
  {
   "start": 46.8,
   "end": 50.58,
   "text": "But stand them up and you've turned dinner into a funeral, which is exactly why."
  }
 ]
}